            <tr>
              <td style=""><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                <tr>
                  <td width="98%" valign="top" class="bottomshade">                    <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                      
                     
                    <!-- Start Code Here -->   
                      
                      
                      
                      <tr>
                        <td class="profileboxtop"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="0">
                          <tr>
                            <td width="22%"><img src="../images/MBA Web/staff/Prof Kumarage.jpg" width="138" height="152" class="normal" /></td>
                            <td width="78%" style="padding-left:20px; text-align:left">
                              
                              <p><strong><A href="http://www.tlm.mrt.ac.lk/staff/Prof_Amal_S_Kumarage.php">Senior Professor Amal Kumarage</A></strong></span></p>
                              
                              <p class="subtext" >
BScEng (Moratuwa), PhD (Calgary), FCILT, CEng, MIE (SL)
</p>
                              
                              
                              <p>Senior Professor, Department of Transport and Logistics Management, University of Moratuwa</p>
                              <p align="justify">Amal S. Kumarage is a Chartered Civil Engineer, Fellow of the Chartered Institute of Logistics and Transport (CILT), Senior Professor in the Department of Transport & Logistics Management at the University of Moratuwa and Honorary Professor at the University of Wollongong, Australia. He is also the Chairman, National Transport Commission and an International Vice President of CILT's global body. In an advisory capacity to the Government of Sri Lanka, he has been instrumental in several important policy, strategy and feasibility studies in transport, highways, urban development and planning sectors. He has also served as an Advisor to the Governments of the Maldives and undertaken studies for the World Bank, ADB and JICA in Sri Lanka and other countries.

</p>                              </td>
                            </tr>
                          </table></td>
                        </tr>
                      
