</p>
                              
                              
                             
                              <p align="justify">Eng. (Dr.) T. Sivakumar is a senior lecturer and the head of the Department of Transport and Logistics Management, Faculty of Engineering, University of Moratuwa. He holds a Bachelor of Science of Engineering Honours Degree in Civil Engineering from the University of Peradeniya and a Master of Engineering degree in Transportation Engineering from the Asian Institute of Technology. He holds a Doctor of Engineering degree in Transportation Engineering from Yokohama National University, Japan.  His research interests are public transportation and Advance transit systems, traffic engineering, urban transport planning, transport modeling and demand forecasting, optimization, road safety, user behaviors and behavioral analysis, transport survey,  etc. He is the founding secretary of the Sri Lankan Society of Transport and Logistics (SLSTL). In addition, he has been involved with several consultancy projects for Road development Authority. National Transport commission (NTC), Ministry of Transport (MoT) and Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA).
